---
description: Scheduler, local-time behavior, and logging
globs:
  - "src/main/scheduler/**"
  - "src/main/logging/**"
  - "**/*schedule*"
  - "**/*log*"
---

# Scheduler rules
- Schedules are defined in LOCAL time (user's OS timezone).
- Handle DST transitions:
  - Don’t duplicate runs unexpectedly
  - Don’t silently skip without logging a warning
- Persist schedule state so app restarts do not lose queued runs.

# Logging rules
- Structured logs (level, timestamp, module, jobId).
- Redact sensitive values (tokens, refresh tokens, cookies).
- Keep user-facing “activity log” separate from debug logs if possible.
